/* Language and script */ Fake false-link claim removed. Shavkunov is not a linguist. And he did not study the language of this state. And all Russian historiography knows that the writing in Bohai is Chinese characters, but used phonetically
/* Government and culture */ The source says only about the southern region. Previously owned by Goguryeo. In Russia, the object of this state has very little resemblance to Goguryeo.

/* Government and culture */ This is not a generally accepted point of view, most works from countries other than Korea show that the ruling class was of the same nationality as the general population. This is also indicated by the language of the documents.
/* Fall */ Hwandan Gogi - supporters of this ideology, not scientists, consider the theory of the eruption of Paektu to be real.
/* Founding */ And Vovin is not a historian and has changed his position many times. Vovin is a linguist by profession.
The language is definitely not classified. Therefore, it is questionable.
The prevailing state language in which the documentation was kept must be indicated first. Minority languages after.
